## Visual No-Gos

{% for nogo in VISUAL_NO_GOS %}
- ❌ {{nogo}}
{% endfor %}

Examples:
- Arrows flowing backward (only forward or loop-back)
- Orphan nodes (every node must have in/out edges or be terminal)
- Unclosed branches (every decision must have all exits)
- Direct cross-swimlane arrow jumps (use handoff nodes)

---

## Rendering Rules (for auto-generation)

1. Parse L1.4 `steps[]` array → create one node per step
2. Parse L1.7 RACIO matrix → group nodes into swimlanes by role
3. Parse `steps[].next` → create edges between nodes
4. Parse `steps[].loop_back_target` → create loop-back edges (dashed)
5. Apply color semantics based on step type (manual/auto/exception)
6. Add start/end terminal nodes
